  <h1 class="Article-title">Font sizes</h1>
  <p class="Text--lead">Overview of the default font size settings and how to use them.</p>

  <hr class="Article-divider">

  <h2 id="section:overview"><a herf="#section:overview" class="Text--resetLink">Overview</a></h2>

  <p>Our approach to font sizes is inspired by <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/gel/guidelines/typography">BBC's gel typography guidelines</a>.</p>
  <p>We use a single type hierarchy that is scaled to work across all devices. We change type sizes based on screen size and device capabilities, such as whether it has a touch screen.</p>

  <p>Settings for the default font-sizes can be found in <code>stylesheets/settings/_settings.font-sizes.scss</code>.</p>

  <div class="docs-example">
